iroptera, nectarivory and cave-dwelling originated several times, but echolocation (used for obstacle detection) evolved only once. Megachiropterans likely originated in SE Asia-Melanesia, and colonized Africa at least four times.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Giannini, Norberto P", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Simmons, Nancy B", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/5bdd9680b22c3726c2c8f31989a208d0", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/344d72b8bbfd42ad2ac97459e0a5c39b2a8f8b8563e74b56447780fef06c0c8f", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/66PJERXZ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/66PJERXZ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/fa0a2e8c1f3b6bf5bf653aa3ac5d13ce!/b218498-221073", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "6", "pages": "496-511", "title": "Cladistics", "volume": "19"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/5bdd9680b22c3726c2c8f31989a208d0"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:66PJERXZ"}, {"identifier": "10.1111/j.1096-0031.2003.tb00385.x"}], "communities": [{"id": "biosyslit"}, {"id": "batlit"}], "relations": {"version": [{"index": 0, "is_last": true, "parent": {"pid_type": "recid